<L>__{exterior bar, downtown k.c. night}
<A>__{truman on the street outside the club at a pay phone. he talks with jack in brooklyn.}
<C>__{truman}
<D>__{i'm just missing this one piece, jack. be patient with me.}
<C>__{jack}
<D>__{how long is that gonna take? why don't you try leaving him alone for a while? come to spain. you can always visit him later.}
<C>__{truman}
<D>__{i don't know.}
<C>__{jack}
<D>__{well, i'm off. i've got my own writing to do.}
<C>__{truman}
<D>__{do it in brooklyn. wait for me.}
<C>__{jack}
<D>__{too many people around.}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{i will leave the address on the kitchen table. truman, what do you do there when you're not with him? it must be awful.}
<A>__{truman's watching a young guy standing outside the bar, looking at him.}
<C>__{jack}
<D>__{think about what i said. join me when you can.}
